A '''conditional dismissal''' is a [[motion (legal)#Motion to dismiss|dismissal]] subject to conditions—for example, the dismissal of a suit for [[foreclosure]] of a [[mortgage law|mortgage]], subject to receipt of payment in the amount of a [[Legal tender|tender]] which induced the dismissal.  [[Thompson v Crains]], 294 Ill 270, 128 NE 508, 12 ALR 931.

