{{Use Australian English|date=June 2018}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}}
The '''Victorian Reports''' ('''VR''') are a series of [[law report]]s which report significant [[Case law|cases]] from the [[Supreme Court of Victoria]] in its [[Original jurisdiction|first decisions]] and [[Appellate jurisdiction|appeal decisions]] [[jurisdiction]]s.

The reports were initially titled the '''Victorian Law Reports''' ('''VLR''') (1875 to 1956), before adopting their present title in 1957.<ref>.{{cite web|url=http://www.lib.monash.edu.au/legal-abbreviations/abb-v.html|title=Monash University Library – Abbreviations of legal publications – VLR|publisher=[[Monash University]]|accessdate=7 February 2011}}</ref> Earlier equivalent reports, published between 1847 and 1851, had been known as "Williams practice cases" and "A'Beckett's reserved judgments".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://guides.slv.vic.gov.au/content.php?pid=50118&sid=368102|title=Law reports – Court cases in Australia – Research Guides at State Library of Victoria|publisher=[[State Library of Victoria]]|accessdate=7 February 2011}}</ref>

In 2016, Little William Bourke commenced publishing the Victorian Reports.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://victorianreports.com.au|title=Victorian Reports Portal|publisher=Little William Bourke |accessdate=8 July 2016}}</ref> The new portal contains both the VRs and the VLRs (1875 to date) in a searchable format.

